    "body": "@dapplion  i don't think it is leading to multiple evaluations of the regenFn's getBlockSlotState called by getAttesterDuties as even if validators processes are parallel, they get queued in the jobProcessor which is single threaded with default maxConcurrency of 1.\r\n\r\nthis is confirmed by the distribution of delta's of duration spend in `getBlockSlotState` during the epoch transitions in both \r\n\r\n16vc prater node:1 validator process, \r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76567250/135035201-7f4ef709-19d4-465b-9f31-550e7b18c717.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n975 prater node : 4 validator processes\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/76567250/135035259-b6902c1a-4aab-4ea9-ba83-21b7ed0aa6d0.png)\r\n\r\nBoth look to have the same distribution delta during epoch transitions: \r\n\r\n`delta(regen_fn_call_duration_sum{entrypoint=\"getBlockSlotState\",caller=\"getDuties\"}[$__rate_interval])`, which basically implies that 4 extra validator duties call in epochs are not really causing any extra or duplicate computation.\r\n\r\neven if the maxConcurrency is increased, there would be no issue as getBlockSlotState's call might get interleaved, but they will still use each other's results as all is happening on a single thread.",
